{
  "AC": "1. GET/POST http://esp32s3-office:5000/dmz/ping performs one signed DMZ sensors POST.\n2. Onboard logs include DMZ status and a useful excerpt of the response body.\n3. Endpoint JSON reports ok/status/body_excerpt (or clear error if sign/time/network fails).\n4. No unsigned POSTs; uses auth.toit Ed25519 path.",
  "ActualSummary": "Implemented /dmz/ping on ESP32 debug server: one signed POST to DMZ using auth.toit + generated secrets seed, with status/body excerpt logged and returned. /healthz now exposes epoch_seconds and auth_ed25519_ready; logs diagnose clock skew. Current board epoch is unsynced (~359k), so /dmz/ping returns 401 invalid signature with clear clock-skew note until NTP sync is added.",
